* ===========================================================================
* mm1_validation.gps   --   GPSS World
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Independent validation model for the Python event-scheduling simulator.
*
* Reference scenario (must match demo_single in queue_sim.py):
*       arrival rate  lambda = 1.00   (mean interarrival 1.00)
*       service rate  mu     = 1.25   (mean service      0.80)
*       servers       c      = 1
*       => utilization rho = lambda/mu = 0.80
*
* Closed-form theory to check against:
*       rho = 0.80 | L = 4.0 | Lq = 3.2 | W = 4.0 | Wq = 3.2
*
* GPSS uses a DIFFERENT random engine and a DIFFERENT modelling paradigm
* (transaction flow) than the Python next-event engine, so agreement of the
* aggregate measures is strong evidence both models are correct.
* ===========================================================================

* ----- two GPSS "Queue" entities are used purely as measurement probes ------
*   SYSTEM : spans the whole sojourn  -> avg contents = L , avg time = W
*   LINE   : spans the waiting only   -> avg contents = Lq, avg time = Wq
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

         GENERATE   (Exponential(1,0,1.0))   ; external arrivals, mean 1.0
         QUEUE      SYSTEM                    ; enter system  (start L/W clock)
         QUEUE      LINE                      ; enter waiting line (start Lq/Wq)
         SEIZE      SERVER                    ; grab the single server
         DEPART     LINE                      ; leave the line (stop Wq clock)
         ADVANCE    (Exponential(2,0,0.8))    ; service time, mean 0.8 = 1/mu
         RELEASE    SERVER                     ; free the server
         DEPART     SYSTEM                     ; leave system (stop W clock)
         TERMINATE                             ; (no count decrement)

* ----- run-length control: a timer transaction ends the run ----------------
         GENERATE   20000                      ; one timer arrives at t=20000
         TERMINATE  1                          ; decrements termination counter

         START      1                          ; run until counter hits 0

* ===========================================================================
* HOW TO READ THE STANDARD REPORT
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*   FACILITY  SERVER   -> "UTIL." column          ......  rho   (expect 0.80)
*   QUEUE     SYSTEM   -> "AVE.CONT." = L (~4.0), "AVE.TIME" = W  (~4.0)
*   QUEUE     LINE     -> "AVE.CONT." = Lq (~3.2),"AVE.TIME" = Wq (~3.2)
*
* The same SNAs are available programmatically, e.g.
*   QM$SYSTEM (max contents), QA$LINE (avg contents), QT$LINE (avg time).
* ===========================================================================

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* OPTIONAL: TRACE VALIDATION
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* To diff GPSS behaviour against the Python TRACE, shorten the run and turn on
* transaction tracing. Replace the run block above with a small batch:
*
*         GENERATE   (Exponential(1,0,1.0)),,,25   ; only 25 customers
*         TRACE                                     ; log every block move
*         QUEUE      SYSTEM
*         ...
*         TERMINATE  1
*         START      25
*
* GPSS then prints, for every transaction, the clock time and the block it
* enters -- which lines up event-for-event with the ARRIVE / SERVICE / DEPART
* lines emitted by queue_sim.py for the same first arrivals.
* ===========================================================================
